  "text": "When the mechanical resonator operates, it will vibrate at a certain frequency that leads to the variation of strain with the variation of temperature. Meanwhile, the heat current is irreversible, which causes the energy loss called thermoelastic dissipation. For most of the resonance gyroscopes, thermoelastic dissipation is one of the key limitations to the Q of gyroscopes [CITATION_1] .",
